A day after the Premier League’s £5.136billion TV deal raised the stakes, Aston Villa decided they could not afford the possibility of relegation.

Villa finally sacked beleaguered manager Paul Lambert on Wednesday night after slipping into the drop zone following their dismal 2-0 defeat at Hull City on Tuesday night.

When there is even more money for the clubs at English football’s top table, decisions like that become a whole lot easier. 

