A statement on the club’s website read: ‘Aston Villa has parted company with manager Paul Lambert. First-team coach Scott Marshall and goalkeeping coach Andy Marshall will continue to prepare the squad for Sunday’s FA Cup tie with Leicester City at Villa Park.’

The players are believed to have been left out of the loop over the sacking and found out via television and social media. Most of them have relegation clauses in their contracts for wage cuts of between 30 and 50 per cent in the event of relegation, so the club are sure to expect an immediate reaction to the change at the helm.

In the short-term, goalkeeping coach Andy Marshall, who has been increasingly vocal in training of late, is likely to play a big role in trying to rally the squad. Lambert’s Premier League record with Villa is woeful. Their 12 goals scored, six per cent shot conversion rate, 67 shots on target and 36 per cent shooting accuracy ranks them worst in the top flight. 

